values:
Against All Authority show tomorrow!!!! YEAH.

So, I don't really have much to say....

I've found that registering for SATs has lifted a huge weight off my shoulders.

I've also found that I really like Sebastian. AND I know what you all are gonna say: "AW, that's so cute!" and thanks ahead of time.....

Life is GOOD.

So, Sebastian and I are together. I really like him. We talk so much more than I have with anyone else...and we talked about that, too.... :)

I don't want Justin to be sad. He's one of my best friends, but I can't help but be pissed off at what he's doing. He shouldn't expect me not to be with the person I really like because he likes me. That's not fair. I kind of wish that he would hate me, but I want him to be the kind of friend that lasts forever, and I'm worried that I've fucked that up.











Don't worry, BE HAPPY.

My sister's gonna train my cats...hahaha....

Without further ado, after months and months of intense fucking search......






.....I FOUND THE BATTERY CHARGER FOR MY VIDEO CAMERA!!!!! NOW, I can spend the $100 that my Mom gave me for my birthday on OTHER things.....

It all started when I looked up the price of a new battery charger online to find that it was $120. I replied," NO FUCKING WAY," and began my search in the living room. After about 5 minutes, I looked in this big basket whose contents are mostly my sister's to find it. I'll admit, I did a little dance....

In other news....I like Sebastian. He knows. Hopefully something will happen.

There's NOTHING to do! Everyone's either working, or has something that they have to do. AND Marcus still hasn't called back.

FREAKIN' CRAP.

BIRTHDAY= 2 days from now

(Way to look over my shoulder while I'm typing, Dad)

Hmmmm...how do I feel right now? I don't really know.....

Eh, the usual: Happy, but with no prominent reason, just everyday life. 

I visited my Grandad (Mom's side) last night. We watched the PGA Tour, Ford Championship to be exact.....it's a golf thing. It was so funny to listen to my 84 year old Grandfather saying,"Oh, Tiger, that was too strong....maybe you can make a bogey out of it." Hehehe...my Grandad's so cute. Then, I went to my Grandma's (Dad's side) and we ate Chinese food, watched the Oscar's, and looked through old pictures. My first baby picture, the one at the hospital, looked so funny. I had a fauxhawk/Alfalfa hairdo. I also got to look at all my Dad's embarrassing school pictures...I say all because ALL of them are really funny looking...and a bunch of pictures of my Mom (she was sooooooooooooo pretty, still is, but back then....damn). AND I saw pictures from my parents' wedding and my baby shower for the first time ever. 

I need to get a fucking job.....

12 days 'til my birthday! March 18th, BITCHES! So, what WILL you get me?

My head hurts....

I was talking with Justin yesterday about our lives. We were really appreciative at the time, and I still am. I have such an awesome life. Good friends, good family, and just good times.....But I was talking with Mike Shope today, and told him that the ONE thing that I would change would be that I would have a boyfriend, a GOOD one, that treats me right, and doesn't break my heart. WHY....love is like a drug, it can hurt you sooooooo much, but you would do pretty much anything to feel it. I DO feel love, but a different kind, and I want more of it.....

I AM really happy....I wish everyone was as happy as this girl right here, but there's no such thing as too happy.....

WORD TO THE WISE: Realize the good things, and appreciate them, God dammit.

My Mom sent me this piece of celestite that's supposed to enhance your dreams if you put it under your pillow. So, I tried it, and the past two nights, I've been having weird ass dreams. Sunday night, I dreamt that there was this guitar playing by itself in my room, and as soon as I went over to check it out, my shoes on the floor started talking to me, and said," You have been courageous in asking about the shawls." When I asked what the fuck they were talking about, they said that I would soon know. Then later, I dreamt that I was having a conversation with a baby doll, but it didn't have a message for me. Then last night, I dreamt that Danny was crippled, but the only reason why was because he was using a walker. Like, the walker was the thing that was crippling him. I felt bad, but it was his own damn fault in the first place. Symbolism?? I think so.

I'm supposed to get my car by this weekend FINA-FUCKING-LLY. Justin's moving into a farmhouse on Saturday. I'm pretty ready for the weekend to be here....

I've been in a relatively good mood the past two days, considering that Danny told me that he actually never liked me....

I'M SO HAPPY IT'S FRIDAY!!!!!!!!!!! I think a really awesome weekend is definitely both needed and in order. The only question is: WHERE'S MY CAR? Oh well, I'm not really worried about it at the moment...the bank is dragging it's ass, and no one can do anything about it.

For those of you who don't know, but care, Justin might be moving into a house out in the country, about fifteen minutes away. It's awesome. It has a fire pit, a garden, a field, woods, and we're gonna put a hammock on the porch, and build a tree house in the tree in his backyard. This spring's going to be so fun!

So, as for that one thing that I could be sad about...pssshhh, fuck being sad!

It would be REAL cool if I could just get someone to cut me open, and fix me.

It seems that after a really awesome day, the only way to go is down.

Today sucked, and yesterday was bad, too. I'm so confused. I feel so emo, and I hate it so much.

I don't think my last update actually updated, but it doesn't really matter because I don't remember what I said....

I got my passport in the mail today. I look funny in the picture, but I'm excited because I can definitely go to Costa Rica now. 

I think I'm supposed to be getting my car later today. SWEET.

I'm pretty happy that this semester's over, but scared about what the next will be like. I hope it's as easy as this one.

Staying home sucks. I hate being sad. I want it to stop, but it's not working too well...I WANT MY CAR.(which I should be getting within the next 2 days)

I think I'm gonna take a bath, or a shower, and wash all this crappiness off.

Winter sucks. I think it's definitely taking the happiness out of me. 

Danny broke up with me today. This Friday the Thirteenth actually did prove to be quite unlucky, for once. I don't think it'll be for long, though. He said he just needs time alone.

I think reading everyone's recent entries gave me a bit of advice that I used to live by, but kind of forgot. 

On another note, my Dad came home last night, and handed me the title to a car. It's a 1992 Volkswagon Cabriolet convertible. My Dad and others are pitching in to get it for me. He said he was going to just get it for me without telling me, but my Grandma said to ask first. SWEET!

I only have ONE reason to be unhappy. Hopefully I won't let that stop me.

My new webshots account...hopefully it works:

http://community.webshots.com/user/theskinnyone

There's some pictures of my Dad, Grandpa, Uncle Vince, me, Danny, and my sister during christmas, and some other cool shit. I plan to update it a whole lot...

I realized today that I ALWAYS expect the worst...which is good, I guess, because then whatever comes out of it is good...unless its exactly what I expected, which usually doesn't happen. 

Zac told me about this show, but I forget all the info., except that van damage is playing....Anybody know which one I'm talking about?



"How you gonna win when you ain't right within?"
I felt like shit this morning, and apparently so did Danny, and my sister....AND my Dad. He took a half day. I love staying home...

Your Monster Profile
Death Cannibal You Feast On: Fried Twinkies You Lurk Around In: Swingers Clubs You Especially Like to Torment: Hippies
What's Your Monster Name?

My sister's watching rap on mtv, and is singing to it!!!! FUUUUCK. This is the most disappointing thing since....ever. There is nothing more depressing than a 7-year-old singing,"Shake that laffy taffy..." Fuck my former stepmom for letting this happen. It WILL stop.

In the year 2006 I resolve to:
Reunite the Spice Girls.

Get your resolution here

SWEET

I had sushi for the first time yesterday! It was great!

On the other hand, what's up with all the tractor trailer accidents? and cops, ambulances, and fire trucks near my house??? what??

I played Ultimate Frisbee yesterday...Tupacs vs. Biggies...The Tupacs were me, Justin, Marcus, and Cat; the Biggies were Mike W., Kelly, Abby, Baby Jet, and Anthony...Guess who won?!??!! TEAM TUPAC!!! YEAH, WE DOMINATED! 4 to 0, BITCHES!!!!!!!WOOOOO!!!!!!

Ok, I'm done.

Oh, pictures from christmas will hopefully be added soon....

A shower with rasberry shower gel, the Shins, and teethbrushing makes for the best shower EVER.

Also, the next time The Rights or Bones Brigade comes to town, party with them.

Apparently there were some crazy goings on including Bones Brigade, The Rights, and the apartment last night. I'm so bummed that I missed it.

Becca gave me a Breakfast at Tiffany's dvd. SWEEET! There was also talking...

Man, Calvin and Hobbes is so cool. Calvin's the little dude with the glasses that I have as a picture. "Cool people wear dark glasses." -Calvin....

I've gotta go read some Calvin and Hobbes now...

Who's going to the show today??? BONES BRIGADE, BITCHES!!!













I miss Danny, and I know, Kelly, I know...it's only a week.

And yes, I do enjoy who I am. Very much so...

YAY. I'm really happy. For those of you who don't know...Danny and I are dating...yeah...that's right...He broke up with Katie because he had been really unhappy for a while, and we liked eachother so....TADA! Hehehe....Danny's so sweet. :)

FOr some reason, I feel really queasy (sp?) right now....I think I miss you guys a lot. I'm coming back in like, two weeks and a day. The summer went sooo fast. I can't believe it. I'm gonna miss my Mom, but still...I love you guys. I'm not as tan as I wanted to be....being an assistant for a photographer does indeed require me to be inside all the time. AND speaking of that photographer...she does all of these photos for this place called Wimberly Glass Works, and they sell jewelry. For their next catalogue, they wanted people to model the jewelry. So, yesterday, my Mom and I were doing what else, but modeling jewelry. SWEET. I'll bring pictures back.

When I get back, we're all gonna do some hardcore hanging out. WORD.

Yo, everyone. How's summer going for you guys? I'm in Texas right now... It's been pretty fun so far, although I miss my friends, shows, well, Pennsylvania in general...

You guys should send me some letters or something:
Rachel Yount
737 Smith Ave.
San Marcos, Tx 78666

I'll send some back to you guys if you give me addresses....it'll give me something to do.

Jeanette: My mom says that you can definitely come down. I still have to talk to my stepdad about others. I don't really see him much. I'm pretty positive about him letting Andrew and Stephen come, though....

CALL ME ON MY CELL PHONE: 421-2583...you'll be able to reach me there unless it's off...

Hopefully I'll talk to you guys soon!

I keep thinking about what happened today and I can't stop. I'll be busy with something and think about it again and believe it's a dream. How could something this horrible happen so close to us. It's so sad. Some kid is going to go to bed tonight knowing that when he or she wakes up in the morning, his or her parents aren't going to be there. I don't know how I could've dealt with that or could deal with that. What really gets to me is that when people love eachother, an argument leads to death? What the hell?

And to top it all off, imagine your little sister being in school when it happened in the parking lot....

So...

I talked to my former step-sister (I guess that's what you'd call it) tonight...it's her birthday, the big thirteen... I might go out to lunch with her on Saturday or something...she's coming up from South Carolina to visit Hannah, my sister...hopefully Mr. Ed won't prohibit our "going out to lunch" thing...I'm excited about that!!!!!!!! YAY!!!!WOOHOO!!!!! WOOOPIIIEE!!!!!! I guess that was a little too excited..more like         a: cool....yeah...

I really like him...I don't know if that's good or bad.....few know what I'm even talking about....mwahahaha

I feel goofy right now...like a goofy goober

YEAH!

So, I'm watching my sister right now...

I got a deviantart account thing. ("theskinnyone") Everytime I get on it, it keeps wanting to verify my email address...telling me that it will send another message to my verified email address to verify it further, but it has yet to get up off of its lazy ass and do it.

Speaking of lazy-asses, I know I've been one for a while. I keep telling people that I'm gonna get a bass (you guys know who you are) and haven't yet...well, I went to triple r and found a bass that I want, but my Dad wants to check out a bunch of basses and see all of the possibilities, which he's supposed to do today. I'm excited, but impatient at the same time because I can't stand letting people down. SO, I'm sorry for waiting so long. I WILL make this happen. SOON....

I went to a show with Jet last night. It was really fun. Afterwards, we went to the Crimson Frog to look up different "Let's Go" songs...we're making a compilation eventually...

Oh, my, Tab is freakin' addicting.....when I got home I still had a little bit of a buzz. I have the theory that Tab just takes all of your energy that you need for the rest of the day and gives it to you the very moment that you take that first disgusted swig of it. Then, afterwards, you fall asleep because you're so damn tired....it's weird....and fun too.

That's pretty much all I have to say. You'll all have to try it sometime. We're thinking of going to Bubba's for my birthday and then drinking lots and lots of Tab....

Now that I think of it, Tab would be real nice for shows too because it gives you so much energy. You'll never stop dancing! AHHHH!!!!

I'm really doubting that this picture will show up, but if it does, it's metamorphosis of narcissus by salvador dali....I might get to see this in person soon!!

It really baffles me that he doesn't care, or at least it seems so, and will probably always seem so.... He doesn't even have the decency ( I think that's how you spell it, but I don't care) to tell me that he doesn't want to hang out or even give me a reason, nope, he just ignores me and acts like nothing ever happened. Having a first love feels like having your only love and it hurts so much to lose them. I know it happens to everyone eventually. I know that the pain will subside, but at the moment, all I can say is," WHY ME??!?!?!?!?!", not to mention that it's Valentine's Day, which I thought would be a good day this year, but apparently not...I need a hug real bad.

So, I saw Kamikaze Zero tonight for the first time in a while, and actually enjoyed it...(don't hate me)

There were lots of stupid kids at the show that kept rubbing their asses against me, and I killed them real hard...

I had this weird dream last night:
I went to this camp in South America. I took all of these things that I would need to survive in the rainforest...and they took them away from me...so, the whole time I was thinking," How will I tell Zac that I'm alive???," but, I don't really know why. It was way weird...

I HAVE NOTHING TO SAY RIGHT NOW!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!AHAHAHAHAHAHAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!

Goodnight....

My Mom's birthday was on Monday. I told her about my bright pink airforce ones...and she laughed and replied with,"When I was your age, I wore cool, yet weird stuff, but that's really cool and really weird...just don't wear them down to Texas, your stepfather would shit..." I told my stepdad about the Adicts show...he said that they sound like a bad band...and I told them about their stage act. He said that they sounded gay, but then preceded to tell me that I should listen to a band from Texas called the "Butthole Surfers"...a bit of contradiction there, eh?

I've been really happy lately, which is good...

I went to a tattoo shop with Nick and others and watched him get his tattoo sort of finished....and I came up with really cool ideas for tattoos that I want to eventually get, with some help from Nick...he said that I should get crossed swords on my back, where I have dimples, so that it looks like the end of the blades actually pierce the skin...awesome...I think I'm gonna do it...

I can't wait until Christmas, even though I don't believe in it....my Mom is getting me cowboy boots...that are awesome....and are surrounded in an aura of greatness...I hope that I get a tri-pod...because I need one...or maybe money towards a video camera...if I get one, I'm bringing it everywhere, so you all should be prepared to be videotaped.

I have a "D" in chemistry, so I need to go do my missing work, so that I get a better grade, and probably more importantly, go out during the week....

I got a new screename: blankexpression2

yep

Well, I think I'm going to just stop talking about people in negative ways, my Mom says that it just gives people even more of the negative tendencies that they have, plus it just pisses me off even more. So, there you have it, I'm going to try...

Show at the Lower Paxton Youth Center on the 12th...The Villains, Decontrol, Craig's band(some of you may refer to him as "Archie"), and some others, too. Everyone must go, and we have no excuse, because we have off the 11th and 12th, so, get rides and go! I think I'll be making flyers...

Oh, this is for Jeanette:
I hope your "getting jaws wired shut" thing was ok..I remembered and missed you o Tuesday...and the other days that I didn't see you, like today...well, I hope you're doing alright!

Until next time...

Well, in order to have a sufficient update, I've decided to back-track a little, fo those of you who haven't know me for a long time...and for my own amusement...

We'll start with eighth grade:
Man, those were the days, Kelly, Steve, Ryan S., and me. We would skate everywhere in Lemoyne and play invisible football at coffee houses. We would pull mageivers (however the hell you spell that) and try to steal flags from the old folks' home. We would have a great time doing it too...and then, near the end of eighth grade, my stepmom cheated on my father and left home. I have to say, I don't think I have, or ever will feel as betrayed as I did then. I sent her letters and emails asking her why she left and got no response and came home only to adjust to living with half of the family I had. 

Then I came to highschool:
I met the most awesome people, those of you that are reading this are included, and have great friends. I went to shows pretty much all year, became friends with Steve again, and met Zac. I realize that I have a wonderful life, although filled with some bad things, like my now ex-stepmom, I reflect on the good and am totally happy. I just want to say," Thank you" to everyone, and I really mean it.

I don't really have much to say anymore...until next time

Hahaha, bastages is in my word count....oh, giggle...

I get to go to the Octuba fest in Carlisle on Saturday...and shop for shoes for homecoming...The Octuba fest has something to do with tubas...yeah...and I'm going with my aunt and grandmother...you guys should show up and we could possibly run into eachother...possibly

I dyed my hair to the natural color, if any of you didn't notice...

not too much going on right now...perhaps later...yeah...

Oh, I forgot, Mr. Ed is coming to visit...woopie

Well, I think that we should all keep livejournal, even after we graduate and get real lives and everything, in order to keep in touch....

SHOW! YAY! I'm bringing my sister...she's so excited...

I really like photo, and that is all I really feel like typing right now...
oh, I just remembered that I didn't feel like updating... sorry...maybe tomorrow

Ok, option A:
I can be responsible and clean and go out and have fun...

Option B:
I can not be resposible and clean and stay home...

Hmmmm....
Option A sounds good to me....

So, I'll see you guys around...probably at the show or something...
Ok, so, I haven't been the best lately, ask me sometime, and perhaps, if you're good, I'll tell you...
